I"Ñ<h2 id="exercise-1">Exercise 1</h2>

<p>Open a Ruby file and create a variable called <code class="highlighter-rouge">pets</code> that holds an Array of three Strings representing the names of pets. Then, write Ruby code to print out the following:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>The pets are &lt;first pet name&gt; and &lt;second pet name&gt; and &lt;third pet name&gt;
The first pet's name ends with a &lt;last letter of first pet's name&gt;.
The second pet's name is &lt;length of pet name&gt; letters long.
The third pet's name &lt;does/does not&gt; contain the letter s.
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>The output in the angle brackets <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt; &gt;</code> should change depending on the values in your <code class="highlighter-rouge">pets</code> array.</p>

