<h2 id="exercise-2">Exercise 2</h2>

<p>Write a program that will ask the user to enter some text.</p>

<ul>
  <li>If the text has an odd number of characters, print â€œODD!â€</li>
  <li>If the text has an even number of characters, print â€œEVEN!â€</li>
  <li>The program should repeat this process until the user enters â€œqâ€ or â€œquitâ€</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Bonus</strong>: Create three versions of this program that use three different types of loops: <code class="highlighter-rouge">while</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">until</code>, and <code class="highlighter-rouge">loop do</code></p>

